\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Non-paying/inactive members
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Many of our members (people who are on So Make It Ltd's official Register
 of Members) have never paid.
 Many have paid just once or twice.
 Many have not attended the space in months, if ever.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Termination of membership
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We currently have no formal process defined for terminating a member's membershi
p (e.g.
 in the event of repeated dangerous behaviour or abuse; or long term absense
 without "leave").
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Pay-as-you-go (PAYG) membership
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Many individuals don't want to commit to paying monthly to use the space
 from time to time.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
No supporter membership
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Some individuals would like to support the space monthly but do not want
 to divulge their address to our membership (UK law requires that all members
 have their address on our Register of Members and all members are entitled
 to view the Register of Members).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Guests don't have a way to "belong" before gaining full membership
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
At the moment if you don't want to be a member there are many ways to stay
 informed but they're all pretty disparate; the only one we really push
 is the newsletter subscription, but that doesn't get a lot of love.
 It would be nice if interested parties could sign up and immediately get
 access to the members area/wiki/etc to make them feel more involved.
\end_layout

