\begin_layout Subsection
Opening the Space
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Only Keyholders can Open the space.
 Simply using their Key may open the Space, or they may be required to perform
 an additional action.
 This additional action can serve two purposes:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Prevent the space being broadcast as open when really the Keyholder just
 popped in to get something.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Getting an idea of how long the Space is likely to be open until (so Members
 and Guests don't waste time visiting the space if it's only likely to be
 open for an hour)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Keyholder who Opens the space must either Close the space when they
 leave; or they must pass on their Closing responsibility to another Keyholder.
 This does mean that a Keyholder may have to kick out Members when they
 leave, but hopefully we can address this in two ways: 1) by having a sufficient
 number of Keyholders, and 2) by having a way of recording how long the
 space is likely to be Open for.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Closing the Space
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The last Keyholder to leave the space must:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Check that no-one remains in the space
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
